    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into strips</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-harissa-charred-pepper-and-jumbo-king-prawn-wholewheat-spaghetti/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>pepper strips</strong> to the pan along with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 7-8 min or until lightly charred</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-harissa-charred-pepper-and-jumbo-king-prawn-wholewheat-spaghetti/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the pepper strips are cooking, add your pasta to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the pasta for 7-9 min (10-12 min for wholewheat)</p><p>or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain the<strong> pasta </strong>and reserve a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-harissa-charred-pepper-and-jumbo-king-prawn-wholewheat-spaghetti/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your<strong> tomato[es] </strong>roughly</p><p>Peel and slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander </strong>finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-harissa-charred-pepper-and-jumbo-king-prawn-wholewheat-spaghetti/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain your <strong>jumbo prawns</strong></p><p>Once the peppers are charred, add the <strong>drained</strong> <strong>jumbo prawns </strong>along with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 3 min</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-harissa-charred-pepper-and-jumbo-king-prawn-wholewheat-spaghetti/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped tomato </strong>and a small splash of <strong>water </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until the tomato is starting to soften and the jumbo prawns are cooked through</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-harissa-charred-pepper-and-jumbo-king-prawn-wholewheat-spaghetti/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the tomato is soft, add your <strong>harissa paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> cr\u00e8me fra\u00eeche</strong>, <strong>drained pasta</strong>, <strong>half </strong>your <strong>ground sumac</strong>, most of the <strong>chopped coriander</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and a splash of <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy harissa, charred pepper & jumbo king prawn pasta</strong></p><p>Tip: If it's looking a little dry add a splash more of the starchy pasta water</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-harissa-charred-pepper-and-jumbo-king-prawn-wholewheat-spaghetti/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy harissa, charred pepper & jumbo king prawn pasta</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>remaining ground sumac</strong>,<strong> remaining chopped coriander</strong> and a generous grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
